description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen to join the Facilities Management Team in a Monitoring Officerrole.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful post holder should have a proactive and friendly attitude and be able to demonstrate previous secretarial/administrative experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Your proven competences will include excellent verbal and written communication skills, combined with strong organisational and team working skills. You will be undertaking a wide range of administrative duties including arranging meetings, preparing agendas, taking minutes and engaging with a variety of staff across the Division.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a permanent full time post (37.5 hours per week – Monday to Friday), however, applicants will need to be flexible with their working days to fulfill service requirements which might include weekend working.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Informal queries, discussions or visits are very welcome, please contactJoshua Ford(FacilitiesDeputy ServiceManageron07795 234729or &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;joshua.ford@nhs.net&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our vision is to provide safe, high quality seamless services delivered with courtesy and respect. To achieve our vision we expect all our staff to uphold our Trust values. Our Trust values are: &lt;br /&gt; Honesty, Openness &amp; Integrity&lt;br /&gt; Fairness&lt;br /&gt; Inclusion &amp; Collaboration&lt;br /&gt; Respect &amp; Dignity&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;***Preference will be given to staff with ‘Priority’ and &#39;At Risk&#39; status including NHS At Risk staff throughout Devon.***&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;DUE TO THE ANTICIPATED HIGH NUMBER OF APPLICATIONS FOR THIS POST WE RESERVE THE RIGHT TO CLOSE THE VACANCY BEFORE THE CLOSING DATE.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
